# CODEOWNERS — auto-route PRs to the right reviewer(s).
# GitHub's CODEOWNERS file — when a PR touches matching paths, the listed
# owners are auto-requested as reviewers. Combined with branch-protection
# rules requiring 1+ approval, this is the auto-merge path.
#
# V107-CI: this file is the routing layer for the agent team. Each
# `mavis/*` owner is a Mavis global agent (see ~/.mavis/agents/<name>/agent.md).
# The agents can also be invoked manually via `mavis team plan run`.
#
# Each path also lists the matching `@4neverCompany/<team>` handle as
# a HUMAN fallback. GitHub's reviewer UI can use these when the
# orchestrator is offline or when a human wants to step in for a
# given PR. The team membership is currently Maurice as the sole
# maintainer on every team; new agents/people get added by inviting
# them to the appropriate team on github.com/orgs/4neverCompany/teams.
#
# Both layers run in parallel:
#   - Agent handles → Mavis orchestrator routes the review
#   - Team handles  → GitHub UI shows a human reviewer (Maurice today)
#
# ─── Default reviewer ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Every PR gets at least the verifier (adversarial) and code-reviewer
# (line-by-line) look. The orchestrator auto-approves if both pass.
*  @mavis/verifier @mavis/code-reviewer @4neverCompany/maintainers

# ─── Domain routing ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
